3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC calculates ETHFI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange applies a ±0.75% funding rate cap to prevent extreme payments. Funding is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with MEXC taking no cut from these payments. Zero maker fees on MEXC make delta-neutral positions more profitable by eliminating entry costs for market makers."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ETHFI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI represents exposure to liquid staking rewards and restaking yields, creating natural funding rate volatility as traders position around staking events and protocol updates. The token's DeFi nature attracts yield-focused traders who often maintain leveraged long positions, leading to consistently positive funding rates. MEXC's early listing advantage for ETHFI provides unique arbitrage opportunities before the token appears on larger exchanges."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI/USDT on MEXC has shown predominantly positive funding rates averaging 0.03-0.08% per 8-hour period during trending markets. Funding spikes occur around Ether.fi protocol updates, restaking reward distributions, and broader DeFi narrative cycles. The pair experiences funding rate compression during sideways price action but maintains positive bias due to the yield-bearing nature of the underlying asset. Weekly patterns show higher funding on weekdays when institutional DeFi activity peaks."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Zero maker fees on MEXC create significant advantages for delta-neutral funding rate capture compared to traditional exchanges charging 0.02-0.04% per side. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities exist between MEXC and Binance ETHFI perpetuals, particularly during funding payment times. The smaller order book requires careful position sizing, but consistent positive funding rates make systematic collection strategies viable. Basis trading between MEXC ETHFI perps and spot holdings on DEXs like Uniswap can capture both funding payments and potential basis convergence."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC's thinner ETHFI liquidity creates elevated slippage risk during volatile periods, requiring smaller position sizes relative to major exchanges. The exchange's regulatory uncertainty adds counterparty risk that must be factored into funding rate arbitrage returns. ETHFI's correlation with ETH staking yields means funding rates can turn negative during broad DeFi selloffs or if staking rewards decline. Smart contract risks from the underlying Ether.fi protocol could impact token valuations and subsequently affect perpetual funding dynamics independent of pure supply-demand factors."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ETHFI/USDT funding payments collected on MEXC?","answer":"MEXC charges ETHFI/USDT funding every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. Positions held during these times automatically pay or receive funding based on the calculated rate and position direction."},{"question":"What makes MEXC competitive for ETHFI funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"MEXC offers zero maker fees for ETHFI/USDT perpetuals, eliminating entry costs that typically reduce funding rate arbitrage profits. This fee advantage, combined with early ETHFI listing, creates unique opportunities not available on larger exchanges."},{"question":"Are there minimum position sizes for ETHFI funding payments on MEXC?","answer":"MEXC has no minimum position size for funding payments, but positions must be held at the exact funding time to qualify. The exchange's 0.1 ETHFI minimum trade size applies to opening positions, making micro-strategies accessible to smaller traders."},{"question":"How does ETHFI's staking yield affect perpetual funding rates?","answer":"ETHFI's connection to Ethereum staking and restaking yields creates natural demand for leveraged long positions, leading to consistently positive funding rates. Higher staking yields typically correlate with increased funding rate premiums as traders seek enhanced exposure."}]}]
